This paper proposes a novel model for joint prediction of entity mentions, event triggers, and arguments using deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper involves the prediction of events, which could make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval, which could make it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
